gemini-2.0-flash-lite.patternDescription: The pattern involves identifying the boundaries (8s) and the core shapes (2s, 3s, 6s, 7s). The output grid is constructed by replacing the internal numbers with a consistent set of numbers (0, 4, 6, 7, 9). The outer boundaries remain as 0s and 8s. The numbers 1 are replaced by 9 and the numbers 2,3,4,6 are replaced by 4, 3, 4, 6 respectively. The numbers 5 are replaced by 0. The numbers 7 are replaced by 7.
gemini-2.0-flash-lite.solvingStrategy: 1. Identify the outer boundary (8s) and the inner shapes (2s, 3s, 6s, 7s). 2. Replace the numbers based on the mapping: 1->9, 2->4, 3->3, 4->4, 5->0, 6->6, 7->7, 8->8, 9->9. 3. Maintain the outer boundaries as 0s and 8s.
hints: Focus on the boundaries and the internal shapes.
Use the mapping to replace the numbers.
The outer boundary is always 0 or 8.
